Female . Bl = 5,5–5,7mm . General habitus ( Fig. 78e ). Head . L = 1,6–1,7mm ; W = 1,7–1,8mm . Head about as wide as long ( Fig. 78a ). Integument black except mandibles sometimes partly reddish-brown. Face shiny and with loose, greyish (to yellowish), erect hairs. Mandibles bidentate. Clypeus and supraclypeal area convex in profile. Clypeus strongly and moderately densely punctate; surface shiny. Clypeoantennal distance 0,3mm . Supraclypeal area sparsely punctate; surface shiny and often marginally chagreened. Paraocular area moderately densely punctate; surface shiny and partly sculptured. Antennae mostly brownish. Mesosoma . L = 1,1–1,2mm ; W (ITS) = 1,2–1,3mm . Integument black. Scutum shiny; surface completely reticulate; disc sparsely punctate (i = 2,0d) ( Fig. 78b ). Scutellum as illustrated in Fig. 78c . Scutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum with whitish to greyish, erect hairs. Basal area of propodeum as illustrated in Fig. 78c ; propodeum and marginal region of posterior truncation shiny; chagreened and reticulate; propodeum with small punctures. Wings . Hyaline. Legs . Integument brownish-black. Vestiture greyish to brownish. Ts coarsely serrate; with 4–5 long, oblique projections ( Fig. 78f ). Bp as illustrated (
Fig. 78g
). Metasoma . L = 2,9–3,0mm; W = 1,8–1,9mm . Integument reddish except the margins of T usually pallid reddish; T1 usually blackish anteriorly; T4–T5 often partly brownish to blackish; margins of T extensively translucent. Apical hair bands absent. Prepygidial fimbria mostly yellowish. Metasomal terga as illustrated in Fig. 78d .
